title: How have the number of calls resulting in an emergency response changed over time?
analysis_commentary: The number of category A calls that result in an emergency response rose from 2.5 million in 2011/12 to 2.9 million in 2013/14, an increase of 14%. Achievement of the target has declined over this period, which might indicate a link. However, the sudden fall in perfromance observed in the firstfour months of 2014/15 is not associated with any sudden increase in call volumes. This suggests other factors are influencing the ability of ambulances to meet their target of attending 75% of category A calls with 8 minutes.
data_source: NHS England, Ambulance Quality Indicators: System Indicators
